### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

@angular/forms

### Description

For signal form, as the `NG_VALIDATORS` (see #64493) is not planned, we need an alternative to integrate our Design System components.

Our components are custom elements that implement `ElementInternals` and integrate the error messages.

Currently, we can't (at least, I wasn't able) implement a directive to bridge the field signal with the custom elements.

### Proposed solution

The expected solution would look like the followingÂ :

```ts
/* suggested directive implementation */
@Directive({
  selector: 'my-input',
  providers: [{ provide: FIELD, useExisting: Field }],
})
export class CustomFieldDirective implements FormValueControl<string>, AfterViewInit {
  value: ModelSignal<string> = model('');

  errors: InputSignal<readonly WithOptionalField<ValidationError>[]> = input(
    [] as readonly WithOptionalField<ValidationError>[],
  );

  elementRef = inject(ElementRef);

  constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      // Here we want to subscribe to the errors signal to inform the customElement accordingly
      this.elementRef.nativeElement.setCustomValidity(
        //ðŸ‘‡ currently, it is never called with field errors
        this.errors()[0]?.message ?? '',
      );
    });
  }

  ngAfterViewInit(): void {
    // Here is the updating of the value signal coming from the CustomElement
    this.elementRef.nativeElement.addEventListener('change', (e: Event) => {
      //ðŸ‘‡ currently, it doesn't affect the form
      this.value.set((e.target as MyInput).value);
    });
  }
}
```

And this directive could be seamlessly used with form signalÂ :

```ts
/* a form component and its custom element example */
// #region create Custom Element
const template = document.createElement('template');
template.innerHTML = `<input /><span id="error"></span>`;

export class MyInput extends HTMLElement {
  static formAssociated = true;

  _internals = this.attachInternals();

  shadow: ShadowRoot;

  constructor() {
    super();
    this.shadow = this.attachShadow({ mode: 'open' });
  }

  connectedCallback() {
    this.shadow.replaceChildren(template.content.cloneNode(true));
    this.shadow.addEventListener('input', (event) => {
      this._internals.setFormValue((event.target as HTMLInputElement).value);
      this.dispatchEvent(new Event('change'));
    });
  }

  public checkValidity(): boolean {
    return this._internals.checkValidity();
  }

  public reportValidity(): boolean {
    return this._internals.reportValidity();
  }

  public get validity(): ValidityState {
    return this._internals.validity;
  }

  public get validationMessage(): string {
    return this._internals.validationMessage;
  }

  public get value(): string {
    return this.shadow.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('input')!.value;
  }

  /*
   * Custom API to inform the Custom Element of a customError
   * valueMissing, patterMismatch, â€¦ could be transmitted through attributes given by the CustomFieldDirective
   */
  public setCustomValidity(msg: string) {
    this._internals.setValidity(
      { customError: msg !== '' },
      msg,
      this.shadow.querySelector('input')!,
    );
    this.shadow.querySelector('#error')!.textContent = this.validationMessage;
  }
}

customElements.define('my-input', MyInput);
// #endregion create Custom Element

@Component({
  selector: 'app-demo',
  imports: [CustomFieldDirective],
  template: `<form (submit)="submit($event)">
    <my-input #foo name="foo" [field]="form.foo"></my-input>
    <button type="submit">OK</button>
  </form>`,
  schemas: [CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA],
})
export class Demo {
  myInput = viewChild('foo');

  protected readonly form = form(
    signal({
      foo: '',
    }),
    (form) => {
      required(form.foo, { message: 'the message' });
    },
  );

  submit(event: SubmitEvent) {
    event.preventDefault();

    //ðŸ‘‡ value wasn't propagated
    console.log(this.form.foo().value());
  }
}
```

### Alternatives considered

The only other alternative I can imagine is implementing an angular component to wrap as a ng-content the custom elements to do the same thingÂ :
```html
<custom-field>
  <my-input name="foo"></my-input>
</custom-field>
```

